# Nimbli UI & Code Rules

## Components

- Reuse existing components before adding new ones.
- Prefer **shadcn/ui** primitives (`Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Dialog`, etc.).
- Introduce a custom component when the same UI appears **more than once**.
- Put reusable UI in `src/components/`. Keep each component small and single-purpose.

## Design

- **Primary color:** `#2bbf9d`.
- Child-friendly, clean, structured layouts; consistent spacing, border-radius, and typography.
- **Styling:** Tailwind utility classes only — **no inline `style` props**; use shadcn/theme tokens where applicable.
- **Mobile-first** breakpoints and layout.

## Code quality

- Avoid long or repetitive code; extract shared pieces.
- Split large components into smaller ones.
- **No business logic inside JSX** — use functions, modules, and **custom hooks** (`src/hooks/`) for Supabase and data flow.
- Ship what the task needs; avoid speculative abstractions.

## File structure

- **Pages:** `src/pages/`
- **Reusable UI:** `src/components/`
- **Data / Supabase / side effects:** `src/hooks/`
- **Context:** `src/context/`

## Naming

- **Components & filenames:** PascalCase, filename matches export (e.g. `ExerciseCard.jsx`).
- **Functions & hooks:** camelCase (e.g. `handleLogin`, `useProfile`).

## Forbidden

- Inline styles (use Tailwind + shadcn).
- Duplicate code that should be shared.
- Monolithic files mixing many unrelated concerns.
- Comments that only restate obvious code.
